It is expected that the number of college graduates in the Beijing area in 2022 will reach 268,000 thousand people - Xinhua News Agency.
At a video conference on the employment and entrepreneurship of college graduates in 2022 held jointly by the Beijing Municipal Education Commission and the Beijing Municipal Human Resources and Social Security Bureau, it was learned that the number of college graduates in the Beijing area in 2022 is expected to reach 268,000, an increase of 16,000 from last year.
The relevant responsible person of Beijing Municipal Human Resources and Social Security Bureau said that they would deploy the employment work of Beijing college graduates from strengthening the matching of supply and demand, strengthening policy support, expanding job channels, ensuring assistance to those in difficulty, supporting innovation and entrepreneurship, and improving service efficiency.
The reporters learned that the Beijing Municipal Human Resources and Social Security Bureau will build a practical platform, increase job supply, actively contact 40 college graduate job experience bases, visit employing units, integrate demand information and job information; focus on the "six in one batch", that is, expanding the recruitment of one batch of public institutions, expanding the recruitment of one batch of state-owned enterprises, expanding the recruitment of one batch of grassroots projects, expanding the recruitment of one batch of volunteers, expanding the employment and internship of one batch, and expanding the one batch of entrepreneurial employment; implement the dynamic management of "one policy for life", recommend no less than 5 job information for each graduate to ensure that 100% of the graduates of difficult families who have the willingness to be employed can be assisted.
